COURSES

The Northeastern University, Boston in the USA, is a private research university. Boston University School of Law was founded in 1898. First-year students attended the YMCA on Huntington Avenue. The school moved to its current home in Fenway - Kenmore Square and became "Northeastern College" before becoming a university in 2013. The school's nine colleges, schools, and departments provide over 200 undergraduate degrees, over 100 graduate degrees, and PhD degrees in pharmacy, medicine and law, among others.
